Government officials had to restore order in Olievenhoutbosch during a mass food distribution scheme. #Day37ofLockdown Courtesy #DStv403 MIDRAND - Gauteng acting social development MEC Panyaza Lesufi said the health of the nation is the priority after government officials had to restore order in Olievenhoutbosch, where crowds gathered for food parcels distributed by the Mahlasedi Foundation. SA Lockdown: Eating dumpster food to survive Social distancing regulations were flouted as scores of people showed up to collect food on Saturday. The MEC said some food parcels will be distributed to individual homes to facilitate social distancing. Government officials worked with the representatives from the foundation to make sure there was an adequate distance between people waiting for assistance. Lesufi said the observation of the government-issued regulations is non-negotiable. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.